The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Saturday, May 01, 2004 				 Gail bottomline swells 15% to Rs 1878 crore
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT 				 	 Banerjee: No pipe-dream																								New Delhi, April 30: Gail (India) Ltd has clocked a net profit of Rs 1,878 crore for the financial year ended March 31, 2004 which represents a 14.6 per cent increase over the corresponding figure of Rs 1,639 crore for in the previous fiscal. 																								The company recorded a net profit of Rs 639 crore during the fourth quarter of the fiscal which is 13 per cent higher than the Rs 563 crore net profit for the same quarter of the previous year.																								The companys turnover for the year reached a record Rs 12,449 crore compared with Rs 11,775 crore in 2002-03. The gross margin has increased to Rs 3,623 crore in 2003-04 against Rs 3,346 crore in the previous year.																								However, problem areas such as the non-reimbursement of central sales tax on LPG, which Gail is currently absorbing, have still not been addressed. Chairman Proshanto Banerjee said the company had to shell out Rs 428 crore under a government directive on LPG subsidy sharing mechanism. 																								Despite this, the market capitalisation and earnings per share of Gail have gone up.																								An increase in polymer and LPG sales has contributed to the increased turnover. The other contributing factors were LPG handling through the Jamnagar-Loni pipeline system, sale of other liquid hydrocarbons and better sales realisation from LPG.																								Natural gas continued to constitute the core business of Gail. Gas sales during 2003-04 were 62.89 MMSCMD against 63.40 MMSCMD in the preceding year. 																								Nestle net dips																								The net profit of Nestle India for the first quarter ended March 31, 2004, has decreased by 13.8 per cent to Rs 64.3 crore compared with the corresponding period last year. Net sales for the period was up by 3.7 per cent at Rs 620 crore. 
